  "Former Google executive, Daisuke Sasaki, usually referred to as 'Dice', is the cofounder and CEO of software developer Freee.",
  "Freee offers cloud-based accounting and HR software for small and medium businesses in Japan. ",
  "Sasaki started the company in 2012 with his friend Ryu Yokoji, a former Sony executive, who's now Freee's chief technology officer.",
  "Freee's share price surged in 2020 as demand for cloud-based services rose amid the pandemic, which forced people to work from home."
